---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Narrative">
  <section class="py-24 px-6 md:px-12 max-w-4xl mx-auto min-h-screen flex flex-col justify-center">
      <div class="mb-12">
        <span class="font-mono text-xs text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4 block">Narrative</span>
        <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-6xl italic leading-tight mb-8">The Intersection of Matter & Light</h1>
      </div>
      
      <div class="font-mono text-sm md:text-base text-gray-300 space-y-8 leading-relaxed text-justify max-w-2xl">
          <p>
              My work exists at the intersection of heavy matter and light. By blending astrophotography, 3D-printed planets, and interactive immersive environments, I seek to create objects that feel like artifacts from a future we haven't yet reached.
          </p>
          <p>
              Each piece in this collection is a study in textureâ€”the 'rocky' grit of physical existence meeting the 'gassy' translucency of our digital lives. These are not just objects; they are environments captured in a state of suspended animation.
          </p>
          <p>
              We are constantly observing, yet rarely seeing. The Observables cycle aims to slow down the act of looking, demanding a recalibration of our senses to perceive the subtle shifts in light, gravity, and time.
          </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 border-t border-white/10 pt-8">
        <a href="/bio" class="font-mono text-xs text-white border-b border-white pb-1 hover:text-indigo-400 hover:border-indigo-400 transition-colors uppercase tracking-widest">
          Read Artist Bio
        </a>
      </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
